<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="2538" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[143,251,983,1007]" box="[143,251,983,1007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[143,251,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[143,201,1023,1047]" box="[143,201,1023,1047]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<emphasis box="[143,201,1023,1047]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[143,1104,1063,1310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">Fastigium verticis with weak and short inflation at hind part. Tegmen protruding beyond apex of posterior femur or not. Left tegmen of male with stridulatory vein stout, a semicircular cell and additional longitudinal vein near stridulatory area in more distal portion of this area; right tegmen of male with rounded mirror, as well as large mirror-like transparent cell and additional longitudinal vein. All femora with one or two spines on genicular lobe. Male subgenital plate with apical lobes widely separated. Usually male genitalia bear a pair of sac-like semi-sclerotized structures provided with numerous small spinules.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="2539" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="2.[143,976,1349,1374]" box="[143,976,1349,1374]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[143,976,1349,1374]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
Key to Chinese species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2005" box="[534,788,1349,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Abaxisotima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[534,675,1349,1374]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">Abaxisotima</emphasis>
Gorochov
</taxonomicName>
(based on males)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[195,1103,1398,1454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<key pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">1. Cercus with rather thick inner branch before apex........................ 2 Cercus without any inner branch before apex............................. 4</key>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[195,1104,1477,1629]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
2. Distal portion of cercus conical, inner branch originates behind middle of cercus.................................................................. 3 Distal portion of cercus widened, lateral margins curled upwards, armed with spinules along margins; inner branch originates before middle of cercus, slightly s-shaped, apex tapered.................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Shi, 2012" authorityName="Wang &amp; Shi" authorityYear="2012" box="[825,1013,1605,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Abaxisotima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocaudata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[825,1013,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">A. macrocaudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1020,1104,1606,1629]" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[195,1104,1653,1709]" lastBlockId="3.[305,1172,167,256]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="2539" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">
3. Apex of cercus acute, inner branch with apex hook-shaped; tegmina extending to apex of posterior femora................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gorochov and Kang)" baseAuthorityName="Gorochov and Kang" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[757,1103,1684,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Abaxisotima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furca">
<emphasis box="[757,846,1685,1709]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="2538">A. furca</emphasis>
(Gorochov and Kang)
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
Apex of cercus comparatively blunt, inner branch long, slightly s-shaped, apex acute; tegmina not extending to apex of posterior femora................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang and Shi" authorityName="Wang and Shi" authorityYear="2009" box="[857,1172,231,256]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Abaxisotima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiniforma">
<emphasis box="[857,1007,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">A. spiniforma</emphasis>
Wang and Shi
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<key pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
<paragraph blockId="3.[263,1172,279,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
4. Pronotum with lower half of lateral lobe darkened. Tegmina with light green stripe along anterior edge, remaining area brown or brownish green. Cercus with a fine subapical spine................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Liu, Zheng and Xia) Pronotum" authorityName="Pronotum" baseAuthorityName="Liu, Zheng and Xia" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Shirakisotima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[816,925,343,367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">A. bicolor</emphasis>
(Liu, Zheng and Xia) Pronotum
</taxonomicName>
with lateral lobe almost uniform, not darkened. Tegmina yellowish green with some dark spots. Cercus without any subapical spine........... 5
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[263,1172,454,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
5. Cercus long, reaching apex of subgenital plate, cylindrical, widened before apex, apex with a pair of sclerotized forcipate spines.......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Shi, 2012" authorityName="Wang &amp; Shi" authorityYear="2012" box="[912,1081,518,542]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Abaxisotima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forcipiforma" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[912,1081,518,542]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">A. forcipiforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1088,1172,519,542]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Cercus shorter, not reaching apex of subgenital plate, apex with acute spine................................................................... 6
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[263,1172,630,813]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">
6. Tegmen length about 27.0 mm. Apex of cercus with short acute spine. Subgenital plate with deep notch on posterior margin, lateral lobe longer than half subgenital plate.................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kang and Yang) Tegmen" authorityName="Tegmen" baseAuthorityName="Kang and Yang" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Ducetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multipunctata">
<emphasis box="[783,969,694,718]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">A. multipunctata</emphasis>
(Kang and Yang) Tegmen
</taxonomicName>
length about 23.0 mm. Apex of cercus with long acute spine. Subgenital plate with shallow notch on posterior margin, lateral lobe shorter than half subgenital plate..................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wang and Liu)" baseAuthorityName="Wang and Liu" box="[852,1172,789,813]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Shirakisotima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevifissa">
<emphasis box="[852,986,789,813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2539">A. brevifissa</emphasis>
(Wang and Liu)
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</key>
